une 3rd however it is not showing up in the portal.','2025-06-20 03:13:23','2025-06-20 03:13:23'),(239,236,0,'my 10k was deposited but its not showing up in the crownmiare portal','2025-06-20 03:15:23','2025-06-20 03:15:23'),(240,236,1,'Updated & Fixed. Thank you for your patience!','2025-06-26 13:09:26','2025-06-26 13:09:26'),(241,237,0,'Hello, \r\n\r\nI do not see interest for this month in my portal. \r\n\r\nPlease let me know.','2025-07-28 08:50:10','2025-07-28 08:50:10'),(242,237,1,'Your time-zone has been updated. Thank you!','2025-07-28 18:41:48','2025-07-28 18:41:48'),(243,238,0,'Hi, checking in on interest for this month.','2025-08-29 02:49:29','2025-08-29 02:49:29'),(244,238,1,'Kindly note: If a payout date falls on a weekend or federal holiday, the dashboard will be paused, and the payout will be reflected on the following business day. We appreciate your understanding.','2025-09-02 10:47:55','2025-09-02 10:47:55'),(245,239,0,'Hi... when withdrawing the interest it shows 10% is taken out when it should be only 5 %... what is the reason for this?','2025-09-04 13:20:15','2025-09-04 13:20:15'),(246,240,0,'Hi... when withdrawing the interest it shows 10% is taken out when it should be only 5 %... what is the reason for this?','2025-09-04 13:20:15','2025-09-04 13:20:15'),(247,239,1,'Hello, Steve Austin here. Let me look into this for you :)','2025-09-04 13:39:20','2025-09-04 13:39:20'),(248,241,0,'hello, \r\n\r\nmy contract says 0 percent management fee... how come the past few months to withdraw I had to pay a management fee? Additionally it says this time it is charging a 5 percent mgmt fee, but when i did the caluclation it is actually coming out to 10 percent. Another issue is that the dashobaord has not been updated since june. i need to see the current statistics of my investmenet. Lastly, I am curious to see if the investmenet can be reallocated to not be so heavy in \"futures\"? if this is possible would it change the interest rate? if yes, how much?','2025-09-09 08:27:52','2025-09-09 08:27:52'),(249,242,0,'hello, \r\n\r\nmy contract says 0 percent management fee... how come the past few months to withdraw I had to pay a management fee? Additionally it says this time it is charging a 5 percent mgmt fee, but when i did the caluclation it is actually coming out to 10 percent. Another issue is that the dashobaord has not been updated since june. i need to see the current statistics of my investmenet. Lastly, I am curious to see if the investmenet can be reallocated to not be so heavy in \"futures\"? if this is possible would it change the interest rate? if yes, how much?','2025-09-09 08:27:53','2025-09-09 08:27:53'),(250,240,1,'Greetings,\r\n\r\nThis is Steve Austin from Crownmaire. IΓÇÖd like to confirm that your account is on a 5% monthly return plan. From this return, 5% is applied as account management fees that is standard across all portfolios in Crownmaire, while applicable taxes (including U.S. taxes in your case) and US bank withdrawal fees are accounted for separately. WeΓÇÖve streamlined the fee structure on your account; you will now only incur the standard 5% management fee plus applicable taxes.\r\n\r\nRest assured your account is being managed with the utmost care to ensure stable, long-term growth.','2025-09-09 12:43:34','2025-09-09 12:43:34'),(251,240,0,'this is not in the contract. i pay taxes myself and additionally this rule is brand new? so as a customer there needs to be a notice before things like this go into affect.','2025-09-09 17:26:24','2025-09-09 17:26:24'),(252,240,1,'Thank you for bringing this to our attention. I have reviewed your account details, and it appears that your profile is categorized under a special family-membership arrangement with direct oversight from our executive board. Because of this, I am unable to access your full contract and supporting documents directly.\r\n\r\nIΓÇÖve escalated this matter to our CIO and CEO for review, and they will provide clarification on the specific deductions youΓÇÖve noted. In the meantime, please rest assured that your account is being carefully managed, and I will keep you updated as soon as I receive further guidance.\r\n\r\nIf you have any additional concerns or questions in the meantime, please donΓÇÖt hesitate to let me know. I am here to assist you.\r\n\r\n- Steve','2025-09-10 14:08:09','2025-09-10 14:08:09'),(253,241,1,'Hello,\r\n\r\nThank you for reaching out and sharing your concerns. After reviewing your account, IΓÇÖd like to clarify that your profile is listed as a special account within our system, belonging to the immediate family of our CEO. Because of this designation, certain details, such as contract terms, fees, allocations, and performance updates, fall under the direct oversight of our executive board rather than the standard support team.\r\n\r\nIΓÇÖd also like to clarify that since this account is not following the standard portfolios at Crownmaire (which are set at 3% monthly), there may occasionally be issues in how your dashboard reflects updates. Unlike standard accounts, which are managed collectively and updated systematically, your account is handled individually at the executive level. However, all records are accurate on our side, and the executive office is reviewing the matters you highlighted.\r\n\r\nI have already escalated your inquiry to the CIO and CEO for review, and they will provide clarification regarding management fees, the calculation discrepancies you noted, and the dashboard updates. Additionally, IΓÇÖve highlighted your question about portfolio reallocation and its potential impact on your rate of return so the executive office can advise accordingly.\r\n\r\nPlease rest assured that your account is a priority, and I will share updates with you as soon as the executive team provides guidance. In the meantime, if you have any other questions or concerns, I remain at your disposal. We will leave this support ticket open until the matter is resolved.\r\n\r\n- Steve Austin','2025-09-10 14:18:49','2025-09-10 14:18:49'),(254,241,1,'Greetings. We have been advised by the Executive Board to arrange a meeting between you and our CEO to directly address your account, contract, and any concerns you may have. The Board has confirmed that the CEO will personally oversee this matter to ensure your needs are fully met. You may reach out to the CEO directly to coordinate this discussion. In the meantime, please donΓÇÖt hesitate to contact us if you have any additional questions or require further assistance.\r\n\r\n- Steve','2025-09-13 15:43:52','2025-09-13 15:43:52'),(255,243,0,'interest isn\'t showing up in my wallet. please lmk','2025-10-31 07:11:40','2025-10-31 07:11:40'),(256,243,1,'Thank you for reaching out. Due to the ongoing U.S. government shutdown, stock market trading activities have been impacted, which has caused temporary delays in processing this monthΓÇÖs interest payouts.\r\n\r\nPlease rest assured that our team is actively monitoring the situation, and all pending payouts will be processed as soon as trading operations stabilize.\r\n\r\nWe sincerely appreciate your patience and understanding during this time.','2025-11-02 21:53:33','2025-11-02 21:53:33'),(257,244,0,'hi! Is the interest being sent? Also please do not send via P2P  my accountant will be unable to decipher the sender of the income. If this is possible that would be very helpful. Also will it be processed today?','2025-11-07 07:11:14','2025-11-07 07:11:14'),(258,244,1,'Thank you for reaching out. Yes, your monthly return is confirmed and will be processed next week. There has been a brief delay this cycle due to the U.S. government shutdown and the resulting market slowdown, which affected clearing and settlement timelines industry-wide. This has impacted our standard disbursement schedule slightly, but all returns remain fully accounted for and on track. We will try to send your payout direct-to-account and not via P2P.\r\n\r\nWe value your trust and consistency with us, and we remain committed to delivering strong performance and continued growth as markets stabilize.\r\nWe appreciate your patience and continued partnership. As our network continues to expand, we look forward to growing alongside partners like yourself who understand the long-term vision.\r\n\r\n- Steve (CSR)','2025-11-07 19:42:57','2025-11-07 19:42:57'),(259,245,0,'Testing','2025-11-07 20:26:37','2025-11-07 20:26:37'),(260,245,1,'Testing','2025-11-07 20:27:12','2025-11-07 20:27:12'),(261,246,0,'Please add the $1815 interest from 11-3-25 to my compounded balance for November!','2025-11-10 11:37:24','2025-11-10 11:37:24'),(262,246,1,'Some payouts are temporarily delayed due to the ongoing government shutdown. Our team is addressing the issue, and we appreciate your patience and understanding as this situation is part of broader market conditions.','2025-11-10 21:18:40','2025-11-10 21:18:40'),(263,244,0,'Hi Steve, The company has reserves that are meant to be used in cases of delays as you have described. Please send the prorated amount by the end of the day.','2025-11-12 03:02:18','2025-11-12 03:02:18'),(264,247,0,'Dear Crownmaire team, \r\n\r\nI need to withdraw a portion of my capital investment as I need cash due to a business I am starting. Please let me know the process of withdrawing $30,000 usd form my capital investment. \r\n\r\nThank you, Aneesa.','2025-11-12 03:04:05','2025-11-12 03:04:05'),(265,248,0,'Thank you for adding the interest for October to my compounded balance!  \r\n\r\nThe only thing I noticed is the next payment needs to change from 11-11 to 11-30!','2025-11-12 11:08:01','2025-11-12 11:08:01'),(266,248,1,'Thank you for bringing this to our attention. We have identified and fixed the issue.\r\n\r\n- Steve (CSR)','2025-11-16 18:15:09','2025-11-16 18:15:09'),(267,244,1,'$2000 have been successfully withdrawn to your bank account. There is a remaining $814 in-transit and should reflect within 1-2 business days. Thank you for your patience and continued trust in Crownmaire Capital.','2025-11-16 18:30:18','2025-11-16 18:30:18'),(268,249,0,'Hi, I have not received a reposnse to my previous support ticket from two weeks ago... additionally, the month of October, interest still has not been complete. I am missing $93. \r\n\r\nAs of today, my returns for the past 30 days need to be deposited. Please take care of these items immediately.','2025-11-28 06:24:37','2025-11-28 06:24:37'),(269,250,0,'The December 1st compound interest is not showing up yet!  Can you fix that please?','2025-12-02 10:46:28','2025-12-02 10:46:28'),(270,250,1,'Greetings,\r\n\r\nMarket uncertainty this quarter has required minor adjustments to our payout schedule. Crownmaire is completing all payouts while safeguarding reserves and keeping overall risk exceptionally low. Your return is secure and will be processed soon. Please expect returns reflected on your portal within the next 24 hours.\r\n\r\n- Steve Austin (CSR)','2025-12-02 17:57:12','2025-12-02 17:57:12'),(271,249,1,'Greetings,\r\n\r\nMarket uncertainty this quarter has required minor adjustments to our payout schedule. Crownmaire is completing all payouts while safeguarding reserves and keeping overall risk exceptionally low. Your return is secure and will be processed soon. Please expect returns reflected on your portal within the next 24 hours.\r\n\r\n- Steve Austin (CSR)','2025-12-02 17:57:45','2025-12-02 17:57:45'),(272,247,0,'HelloΓÇª following up. ItΓÇÖs been a month. No response. Four days. I need it back in the portal as itΓÇÖs been more than 30 days since I requested. And my contract is not even 30 days. ItΓÇÖs less than that. I will be reporting this company if itΓÇÖs not in my wallet in 4 days.','2025-12-04 18:05:33','2025-12-04 18:05:33'),(276,251,0,'Crownmaire was supposed to give compounded returns for last 7 months, yet youΓÇÖve been giving fixed returns for 3 months. Please fix this immediately','2025-12-05 17:02:28','2025-12-05 17:02:28'),(277,247,1,'Your partial capital request is under review and moving through our standard closeout procedure. We will provide the estimated withdrawal timeframe shortly. Thank you for your patience and understanding.\r\n\r\n- Steve (CSR)','2025-12-08 15:56:06','2025-12-08 15:56:06'),(278,251,1,'We understand your concern and are investigating this issue right away. Our team will rectify the return calculation promptly. Thank you for notifying us and for your patience.\r\n\r\n- Steve (CSR)','2025-12-08 16:07:27','2025-12-08 16:07:27'),(280,253,0,'I believe the next return should be 12/31/25 instead of the December 5th shown!','2025-12-18 13:32:01','2025-12-18 13:32:01'),(281,253,1,'Hello,\r\nThank you for flagging this and for reviewing your dashboard closely. Our operations and technology teams are currently updating and reconciling your historical data within the portal. During this process, certain dates or activity may appear temporarily incorrect.\r\nPlease disregard the portal activity over the next one to two weeks while these updates are completed. Once finalized, your dashboard will be fully corrected and synchronized with our internal records.\r\nRest assured, everything will be reflected accurately once the update is complete.\r\n- Steve (CSR)','2025-12-19 04:22:34','2025-12-19 04:22:34'),(282,254,0,'Hello, today is January 2 and I was wondering when the end of December payment will be credited to my account? It shows December 10 th and needs to be adjusted!','2026-01-02 12:45:07','2026-01-02 12:45:07'),(283,255,0,'You changed my payment date from December 10 to February 1st!  I donΓÇÖt not show any interest payments for December. \r\nPlease correct!\r\n\r\nThank you!','2026-01-08 13:54:10','2026-01-08 13:54:10'),(284,255,1,'Thank you for reaching out, and we appreciate you flagging this.\r\n\r\nTo clarify, the December payout experienced a brief processing delay due to heightened market volatility and liquidity management considerations during Q4. While this created some timing discrepancies in the system, all accrued returns for December remain fully accounted for and will be credited accordingly.\r\n\r\nWe have also taken this opportunity to standardize our payout schedule going forward. Effective immediately, all your monthly payouts will be recorded with a fixed credit date of the 1st of each month. If the 1st falls on a weekend or market holiday, the payout will reflect on the next business day, while the reference date will remain unchanged. This ensures consistency, clarity, and better alignment across reporting periods.\r\n\r\nRegarding the date you are seeing, the system update reflects this standardization rather than a loss or omission of returns. Your December interest has not been removed and will be reflected as part of the upcoming credit cycle.\r\n\r\nDespite the operational timing adjustments in Q4, Crownmaire has continued to deliver strong overall performance through challenging market conditions, a period in which many firms materially underperformed. We were able to deliver 33% annual returns for the year 2025 minus the December payout which is only delayed. We appreciate your patience and continued trust as we finalize these adjustments while maintaining disciplined capital and risk management.\r\n\r\nPlease rest assured that your account remains in good standing, and our team is closely monitoring the final credit update. We will keep you informed should anything further be required. It\'s been a great year together despite some quarter 4 complications. We look forward to doing even better for the year 2026!\r\n\r\n- Steve (CSR)','2026-01-16 13:42:33','2026-01-16 13:42:33'),(286,257,0,'Hello, I believe my interest for December is not reflected in my transaction history!','2026-02-09 16:33:15','2026-02-09 16:33:15'),(287,257,1,'Hello Mr. Henges,\r\n\r\nThank you for reaching out. As we work through clearing pending items and normalizing payout schedules, please allow a few additional days for the system to complete synchronization and accurately reflect performance-related gains.\r\n\r\nWe will notify you as soon as the update has been finalized.\r\n\r\n- Steve (CSR)','2026-02-10 15:57:36','2026-02-10 15:57:36'),(288,258,0,'Hello!  Can you correct my statement?  It seems December and February interest payments are missing! \r\n\r\nThank you!','2026-03-02 12:33:38','2026-03-02 12:33:38'),(289,258,1,'Greetings Mr. Henges,\r\n\r\nPlease allow up to a day for the amounts to reflect in your account. Occasionally, time zone differences or minor system delays can affect the exact timing of when updates appear on the dashboard.\r\n\r\nI have checked your account and can confirm that the February return was successfully posted to your account yesterday.\r\n\r\nThank you for your continued trust in Crownmaire. As market conditions remain challenging, our team continues to work diligently to navigate volatility and strive to generate positive returns for you and all our members.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\nSteve (CSR)','2026-03-05 15:44:30','2026-03-05 15:44:30'),(291,260,0,'Hello,  I noticed you credited my account for January and February interest,  however I believe the payout interest from December is still missing! \r\n\r\nThanks in advance!','2026-03-07 17:32:09','2026-03-07 17:32:09'),(292,261,0,'Hello, I never heard back from you on my last support ticket from March 7th!\r\n\r\nAlso can you send me a 1099 tax form for 2025 to submit to my tax people! My email is\r\ntrip.henges1@gmail.com','2026-03-28 22:36:59','2026-03-28 22:36:59'),(293,262,0,'Hello, It seems that interest from December and March are not included in the transaction history!  Can you look into that and let me know?\r\n\r\nThanks in advance!','2026-04-05 15:15:47','2026-04-05 15:15:47'),(294,263,0,'March return not received. Please check','2026-04-09 10:46:26','2026-04-09 10:46:26'),(295,261,1,'Good day Mr. Henges. 1099 has been sent over to your email!','2026-04-09 23:13:54','2026-04-09 23:13:54'),(296,262,1,'Hello Mr. Henges,\r\n\r\nThank you for your patience. The return for last month has now been successfully posted to your account.\r\n\r\nWe appreciate your understanding as we navigate challenging global market conditions due to the wars. Our team continues to manage volatility and broader macroeconomic pressures with a disciplined approach, and we remain focused on maintaining stability and consistency in performance.\r\n\r\nAny recent delays in reflections or variations in returns are part of this adjustment period and are expected to normalize as conditions stabilize globally\r\n\r\n- Steve (CSR).','2026-04-09 23:20:26','2026-04-09 23:20:26'),(297,262,0,'Hello, thanks for getting back to me! I looked at my transactions and I see you changed the payout date to May, however it show a zero dollar amount for March interest, and December is still missing!','2026-04-10 12:13:20','2026-04-10 12:13:20'),(298,262,1,'Mr. Henges, we are still working on recovering past profits (in your case, December). As for March return, it should update shortly and reflect as we have already posted it from the backend systems and trading accounts. Give it a few hours and then refresh, it should show up.\r\n\r\nBest - Steve (CSR)','2026-04-10 17:52:30','2026-04-10 17:52:30'),(299,264,0,'Hello again! It seems I still have not received interest for December, and April!  Also the March interest recorded was $955 instead of the typical $2500! Also I have had my $100k invested for one year now, and only have approximately $22k for interest, and if my return is 3% I believe it should be $36k for 12 months, not $22k!','2026-05-17 10:56:03','2026-05-17 10:56:03'),(300,264,1,'Greetings Mr. Gordon, \r\n\r\nThank you for your message. I have reviewed your account and the overall portfolio performance history, and IΓÇÖd like to provide some clarification regarding the recent distributions and returns. \r\n\r\nCrownmaire operates with a targeted monthly return objective of approximately 3%; however, these targets are not fixed or guaranteed and remain dependent on broader market conditions and portfolio performance. Over the past few months, global macroeconomic and geopolitical developments have created unusually challenging trading conditions across financial markets.\r\n\r\nAs part of the firmΓÇÖs risk management and capital preservation approach, the December distribution cycle was intentionally withheld in order to reduce overall performance pressure and stabilize portfolio positioning going into the new year. As a result, the fund closed the year at approximately 33% overall delivery rather than the full 36% target projection.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, during the last two months, heightened volatility related to ongoing global conflicts and market instability led the firm to prioritize capital protection and risk reduction over aggressive return generation, which is reflected in the lower March performance.\r\n\r\nOur primary objective remains the long-term preservation and responsible management of member capital during difficult market environments, while continuing to position the portfolio for normalized performance as conditions improve. We have managed to kept ourselves in the green despite the conditions and rest assured, once the markets stabilize more and the firms performance is back on track, everything will return back to normal and we will work on adjusting the differences as soon as possible! Once again thank you for your trust and patience Mr. Gordan.\r\n\r\nPlease let us know if you have any further questions and we would be happy to assist further.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\nSteve (CSR)','2026-05-22 12:33:59','2026-05-22 12:33:59');
